        "content": "<p>We recently added a new animation that flashes a message's body when the message is edited.  This is the feedback thread for that change.<br>\n(Note: You may need to reload to see this working correctly; there was a bug in the initial deploy that flashed many messages that shouldn't be)</p>",
        "id": 191059,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1492799747
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Playing with the edit feature made me notice a little detail:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/29/xmwy3G4Z8b9Kd9S5iiEJ8S_S/pasted_image.png\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"pasted_image.png\">pasted image</a> <br>\nThe textarea has the little mark in the bottom right that usually means you can drag to resize it, but it isn't actually resizable as far as I can tell.<br>\nShould we just get rid of that mark?</p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/29/xmwy3G4Z8b9Kd9S5iiEJ8S_S/pasted_image.png\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"pasted image\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/29/xmwy3G4Z8b9Kd9S5iiEJ8S_S/pasted_image.png\"></a></div>",
